tutorialEntries:
Our first of two types of "Conditional Statements" is the while-Statement:
while(<condition>) {
	<consequent>
}
For our purposes write "while (true) {" and then press Enter. That means we want to repeat the following code infinitely! But don't worry it won't take infinitely to complete this level!

Inside your while-Statement you need this:
	if (<knight name>.canMove()){
		<knight name>.move();
	}
	else if (<knight name>.targetCellIs(EXIT)){
		<knight name>.useItem();
	}
	else {
		<knight name>.turn(RIGHT);
	}
